gencode.v16.annotation.gtf is the original ENCODE gtf file and can be obtained here:
ftp://ftp.sanger.ac.uk/pub/gencode/release_16/gencode.v16.annotation.gtf.gz

I used make-tables.R
to extract the transcripts and genes and make two new tables.

gencode.v16.annotation.genes.txt.gz
gencode.v16.annotation.transcripts.txt.gz

These tables are subsets of the original expect 
1- the first column is a unique ID
2- the last column tells what row of the original gtf files corresponds to the row in this file.

